  "text": "HomeShoppingThe Santa Monica-based brand has centered naturally-derived ingredients like active plant enzymes and essential oils for more than 30 years.Photo: Courtesy of SonägeBrand Bio is Fashionista's guide to the best independent fashion and beauty brands — a resource for retailers, job seekers, B2B companies and consumers alike. If you'd like your brand to be featured, fill out this form.SonägeHeadquarters: Santa Monica, CAE-commerce: sonage.comSocial Media: Instagram / TikTok / FacebookWhat: A California-based skin-care brand that focuses on effective products made with natural alternatives that aim to deliver a soothing, spa-like experience.Price Range: $20-$70Founder: Anisha KhannaOrigin Story: Inspired by her upbringing in India and Ayurvedic traditions, Anisha Khanna founded her skin-care brand Sonäge in 1994. Sonäge gets its name from the French expression \"Bien porter son âge,\" which translates to, \"To look good for one's age.\" Scroll to ContinueRecommended ArticlesThe \"spa-grade\" brand balances skin-care science with curated botanical ingredients. The formulas draw on Ayurvedic ingredients and modern science to create products using natural options such as burdock root, honeysuckle and tea tree oil. With products made in small batches every 90 days, Sonäge also formulates its skin-care products with active plant enzymes and pure essential oils.Photo: Courtesy of SonägeStockists: Amazon, Walmart and professional spasHero Products: Glow To Go Glycolic Acid Peel Pads ($30), Refixion Sans Retinol Crème ($60), Vitality Nourishing Facial Oil ($48), C Shield Smart Serum ($48)PR Representation: AMD-PRHow to get in touch: Contact formWant your brand featured? Hit the link below.Please note: Occasionally, we use affiliate links on our site. This in no way affects our editorial decision-making.Subscribe to Our Newsletter",
